race.comment: CHINO LA DIVA (1) jumped straight to the lead from the inside draw and led until the final turn before weakening to finish ninth over 1500m at Ascot 15 days ago. She is Likely to push forward again, and with a big drop in class here, she could take them all the way this time. BONNY ROCK (4) had been flying with back-to-back wins in the country, but last start finished well back over 1200m at Ascot in a far stronger field. She faces an easier task here, and from a superior gate, she should go close to taking this out. WONSHOT (9) was unplaced when resuming, and then last time out finished sixth over 1200m here, just over 2 lengths off the winner when racing close to the pace throughout. He is peaking third up, so stick with him. JUST GIFTED (3) ended her last prep as a winner, and shapes as a genuine chance first-up.
